      "span_text": "In the case of Silene dioica, the fungus, Microbotrium violaceum, does exist within the specific plant tissues that were examined with the employment of NIR spectroscopy; thus, the detected spectral alteration was explained by chemical alteration occurring because of the chemical structure of the fungus or the host plant's reaction to it [CITATION_1] ."
